Data visualization is a term used to describe the practice of depictingtext-based data in visual context
Its is a business analytics tool. 

Why data vis?
1. We can't really see/process data using only spreadsheets
2. The "picture superiority effect" - phenomenon when a person is able to recall the visual content better than text content.
3. Able to provide the info to the Decision maker easily and quickly.

Difference b/w Business Intelligence and Data Visualization:

BI - Set of tools  and techniques used to convert raw data from various DBs into meaningful info
Data viz - creating visual representation of data.
